Below is an overview of the work we will perform:

Roof: We will install SOLARSPAN insulated sheeting in woodland grey, along with various Colorbond flashing and trimclad materials to ensure a durable and weather-resistant roofing solution. Additionally, we will install roof battens and squareline gutters to enhance the functionality and aesthetics of your roof. For the back roof we will install trimclad sheeting where needed. 

Fascia & Gutter: This includes the installation of squareline gutters and G.P brackets to ensure proper water drainage and structural support.

Safety & Compliance: We prioritise safety in our projects, which includes edge protection, QBCC home warranty insurance, and tie-down builders strapping as per regulations. Furthermore, crane delivery of sheets will ensure safe and efficient handling of materials on-site.

Optional: Extras: We offer Ecotuff insulation blankets as an additional option to enhance thermal efficiency in your roofing system.

If you have any questions or wish to discuss further details, please don’t hesitate to reach out.

RE ROOF QUOTE for 33 Charles St, New Farm.

 


Materials included in the quote are BlueScope steel Zincalume, Ecolife anticon insulation and Bremick vortex screws and Admil proseal silicone.

 

See the image attached (blue section) for proposed replacement. Excludes the flat back roof as its in good condition and the window hood roofs (Not an immediate concern, poor condition).

 

All quantities are measured in lineal or square meters.

 

Our quote for supply and install all roofing materials. Removal of existing roof related rubbish will be removed and disposed of on completion.

 

See optional extras included below - We will reuse the whirlybirds if the fit the new roof sheets and are not damaged while removing due to excessive silicone.

 

We provide a 10 year workmanship guarantee and a product warranty of up to 35 years* (product warranty is determined by various factors (pitch of roof, salt water proximity and product type) and will be issued by BlueScope steel upon completion).

 

QBCC home warranty insurance will be lodged on your behalf within 10 days of receipt of deposit. 

 

If you're happy with the quote we require a 20% deposit to lock in your job.

RE ROOF QUOTE for 15 Llewellyn Street, New Farm, QLD 4005.

 

Materials included in the quote are BlueScope steel Zincalume, Ecolife anticon insulation and Bremick vortex screws and Admil proseal silicone.

 

See the image attached (blue section, includes lower back roof) for proposed replacement. Does not include the asbestos roof. 

 

All quantities are measured in lineal or square meters.

 

Our quote for supply and install all roofing materials. Removal of existing roof related rubbish will be removed and disposed of on completion.

 

See optional extras included below - gutters are not essential as they still have some life left but should be considered while ground up scaffolding is in place. 

 

We provide a 10 year workmanship guarantee and a product warranty of up to 35 years* (product warranty is determined by various factors (pitch of roof, salt water proximity and product type) and will be issued by BlueScope steel upon completion).

 

QBCC home warranty insurance will be lodged on your behalf within 10 days of receipt of deposit. 

 

If you're happy with the quote we require a 10% deposit to lock in your job.

See the image attached (blue section, includes lower back roof) for proposed replacement. Does not include the asbestos roof. 

 

All quantities are measured in lineal or square meters.

 

Our quote for supply and install all roofing materials. Removal of existing roof related rubbish will be removed and disposed of on completion.

 

See optional extras included below - gutters are not essential as they still have some life left but should be considered while ground up scaffolding is in place. 

 

We provide a 10 year workmanship guarantee and a product warranty of up to 35 years* (product warranty is determined by various factors (pitch of roof, salt water proximity and product type) and will be issued by BlueScope steel upon completion).

 

QBCC home warranty insurance will be lodged on your behalf within 10 days of receipt of deposit. 

 

If you're happy with the quote we require a 10% deposit to lock in your job.

Description:
UPDATED QUOTE FOR RE-ROOF STAGE 1 (see attachment for proposed area). 

 

As per plans provided on 07/05/25 by Clarissa - existing demotion cladding area page A3001. There are no specifics given for reason to change other than "existing screening to be removed" as per plans provided. Please provide details for area to quote wall cladding separate.

 

Since acceptance of the original quote (QT00540) and doing the check measure on Thursday 04/12/25, SBL Roofing has been made aware that internal fit outs - gyp rock, electrical works have commenced.  Typical works start from the roofing and work down from there, therefore SBL Roofing will not be held responsible for any internal water ingress damages caused to new or pre existing structure and or materials. 

 

This quote includes all new roofing materials adheres to the QLD building codes and standards ie. minimum pitch requirements and box gutter/sump requirements as per hydraulics plans provided on 17/11/25. Quote "QT00540" was accepted with no hydraulics plans provided and was based on assumption and trying to obtain these plans for some time prior.

 

Proposed newly installed box gutter brackets and floor to meet AS/NZS 3500.3 Provisions.ie. correct fall to sumps/outlets. See photos attached for current non compliant box gutter system.

 

Box gutter brackets - maximum of 750 mm spacing for box gutter brackets using a discontinuous support system is in line with the referenced standards for Queensland (QLD)building and construction compliance.
